  "doc_id": "13360",
  "text": "In other systems G1/S transition is controlled in part by factors that regulate cell growth such as CycD or Myc [CITATION_1] . Curiously, CycD does not seem to be critical for endocycles in follicle cells (see Materials and methods). This presents a paradox because CycD is known to be critical for cellular growth in Drosophila [CITATION_2] and a key feature of all endocycles is an increase in cell size. Interestingly, the expression screen described previously (Table 1) [CITATION_3] might provide an answer to this apparent paradox, because this screen demonstrated that Myc, another component required for growth, is transcriptionally upregulated at the transition.",
